verbose_text: Then we verified the impression of miR-139-5p on the levels of Wnt1, p-GSK-3beta, GSK-3beta and beta-catenin, and the results indicated that the Wnt1, beta-catenin and the phosphorylated GSK-3beta levels in miR-139-5p-overexpressing cells were downregulated while the GSK-3beta was inversely upregulated (XREF_FIG), which indicates that miR-139-5p may inhibit the Wnt / beta-catenin pathway.
